# ─── Line-ending normalization ──────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Every text file is stored with LF line endings regardless of the platform
# git is running on. Without this, Windows checkouts with historical
# autocrlf settings can re-commit files with CRLF endings and produce
# unreviewable diffs — see #235 for a real-world instance where three
# shipper-core source files flipped to CRLF and showed thousands of
# "line changes" that were actually pure line-ending churn.
#
# `text=auto` lets git detect binary vs text; `eof=lf` forces LF on
# committed text. Working-tree files may still be CRLF on Windows; that is
# fine — only what is stored matters.

* text=auto eol=lf

# ─── Machine-generated policy artifacts ─────────────────────────────────────
#
# `linguist-generated=true` hides these from GitHub's "files changed"
# default view (they show up but collapsed) and excludes them from
# language statistics.

policy/no-panic-baseline.json linguist-generated=true
badges/*.json                 linguist-generated=true
